# Unit Testing Patterns

## 📌 PURPOSE

Defines unit testing standards using TDD (Test Driven Development).

Ensures reliable, maintainable, and testable code.

---

## 🚨 TDD (MANDATORY)

### DO

Follow strict TDD cycle:

```id="tddflow"
1. Write failing test
2. Run test (FAIL)
3. Implement minimal code
4. Run test (PASS)
5. Refactor
```

### DO NOT

* Do not write production code without test
* Do not skip failing test step

---

## 🧱 TEST STRUCTURE

### DO

* Place tests in:

```id="testpath"
src/test/java/com/example/tasktracker
```

* Mirror main package structure

---

## ⚙️ TESTING STACK

### DO

* Use:

  * JUnit 5
  * Mockito

---

## 🧪 SERVICE TESTING (PRIMARY FOCUS)

### DO

* Test service layer thoroughly
* Mock repository layer

### EXAMPLE

```java id="servicetest"
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class TaskServiceTest {

    @Mock
    private TaskRepository repository;

    @InjectMocks
    private TaskService service;

    @Test
    void shouldReturnTaskWhenFound() {
        Task task = new Task(1L, "Test");

        when(repository.findById(1L)).thenReturn(Optional.of(task));

        TaskResponse result = service.getTask(1L);

        assertNotNull(result);
    }
}
```

---

## 🎯 TEST CASE RULES

### DO

* Cover:

  * Success cases
  * Failure cases
  * Edge cases

### EXAMPLES

* Task found ✅
* Task not found ❌
* Invalid input ❌

---

## ❗ EXCEPTION TESTING

### DO

* Verify exceptions

### EXAMPLE

```java id="exceptiontest"
@Test
void shouldThrowNotFound() {
    when(repository.findById(1L)).thenReturn(Optional.empty());

    assertThrows(ResourceNotFoundException.class,
        () -> service.getTask(1L));
}
```

---

## 🧪 CONTROLLER TESTING

### DO

* Use MockMvc
* Mock service layer

### EXAMPLE

```java id="controllertest"
@WebMvcTest(TaskController.class)
class TaskControllerTest {

    @Autowired
    private MockMvc mockMvc;

    @MockBean
    private TaskService service;

    @Test
    void shouldReturnTasks() throws Exception {
        mockMvc.perform(get("/v1/tasks"))
            .andExpect(status().isOk());
    }
}
```

---

## 🔄 NAMING CONVENTION

### DO

* Use clear names:

```id="naming"
shouldCreateTask
shouldReturnTask
shouldThrowNotFound
```

---

## 🚫 DO NOT RULES

* Do not test repository directly (unit tests)
* Do not use real database in unit tests
* Do not write large integration-style unit tests
* Do not skip edge cases

---

## ⚙️ BEST PRACTICES

### DO

* Keep tests small and focused
* Mock dependencies
* Use descriptive assertions
* One behavior per test

---

## 📊 COVERAGE RULES

### DO

* Cover all service methods
* Cover exception paths

---

## 🧠 AI ENFORCEMENT RULES

* MUST follow TDD cycle
* MUST write test before implementation
* MUST test service layer
* MUST mock dependencies
* MUST test failure scenarios
* MUST NOT write code without tests

